import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year

    yearly_data = data.groupby(['year', 'series']).mean().reset_index()

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    for industry in yearly_data['series'].unique():
        industry_data = yearly_data[yearly_data['series'] == industry]
        plt.plot(industry_data['year'], industry_data['rate'], label=industry)

    plt.title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rate across all industries from 2000 to 2010?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.legend(title='Industry', loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(range(2000, 2011))
    plt.grid(True)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    max_rate_industry = data.loc[data['rate'].idxmax()]['series']
    max_rate = data['rate'].max()
    
    industry_rate = data.groupby('series')['rate'].max().sort_values(ascending=False)
    colors = ['red' if industry == max_rate_industry else 'blue' for industry in industry_rate.index]
    
    plt.bar(industry_rate.index, industry_rate, color=colors)
    plt.axhline(max_rate, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Rate: {max_rate:.2f}')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Industry')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.title('Which industry has the highest unemployment rate in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Unemployment Rate')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['rate'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unemployment rate across all industries?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
